'''David MacIntyre''' (1952 - ) is a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[composer]] based in [[Vancouver]]. He is a professor of Music Composition at [[Simon Fraser University]] in [[Burnaby]]. 

==Style==

MacIntyre is predominantly known as a composer for voice, with successful operas, art songs, and pieces for choir. His works are noted for their lyricism and rhythmic vitality.

==Selected works==
* "Sisyphus" (1983)
* ''The Architect" (1994)
* "Ave Maria" (1994)

